    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Standard measurement of the weight of gemstones, equal to 0.200 grams. Until 1913, the carat's weight varied in different countries, generally defined around 3.17 grains.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
